    "Ibrahim and Meawad [97] and Patel et al. [98] reported that soda-lime and fine glass powders slightly delay the setting time but increase workability, especially at lower replacement levels.",
    "However, higher glass content may reduce fluidity.",
    "Baikerikar et al. [99] found that while adding WGP and sand improves workability, higher glass powder levels can lead to a slight slump reduction and delay in setting time.",
    "Other study by jiang et al. [40]investigated of replacement cement by WGP (0-30)% replacement ratio found that the workability improvement and prolonged the setting time, and when exposed to higher temperature it found that the bonding strength and compressive strength increased.",
    "Table 11 demonstrates how the inclusion of WGP as an SCM influences fresh, mechanical, and durability characteristics."
